[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2:1-55 Genealogies. - We are now come to the register of the children of Israel, that distinguished people, who were to dwell alone, and not be reckoned among the nations. But now, in Christ, all are welcome to his salvation who come to him; all have equal privileges according to their faith in him, their love and devotedness to him. All that is truly valuable consists in the favour, peace, and image of God, and a life spent to his glory, in promoting the welfare of our fellow-creatures.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A third line of descent from Caleb, the son of Hezron, the issue probably of a different mother, perhaps Jerioth ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 2:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The supposed omissions in this verse have been supplied as follows:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(1) \"Mesha, the father of Ziph; and the sons of Ziph, Mareshah, the father of Hebron;\" or",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) \"Mareshah, the father of Ziph; and the sons of Mareshah, the father of Ziph, Hebron.\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ziph, like Jorkoam 1 Chronicles 2:44 and Beth-zur 1 Chronicles 2:45, is the name of a place where the respective chiefs (\"fathers\") settled. Similarly Madmannah, Machbenah, and Gibea 1 Chronicles 2:49, Kirjath-jearim (Joshua 9:17 note), Bethlehem and Beth-gader (Jedur, 1 Chronicles 2:51) are unmistakeable names of places in the list, names which it is not probable were ever borne by persons. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Ziph, like Jorkoam ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 2:44",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and Beth-zur ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 2:45",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", is the name of a place where the respective chiefs (\"fathers\") settled. Similarly Madmannah, Machbenah, and Gibea ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 2:49",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", Kirjath-jearim (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 9:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " note), Bethlehem and Beth-gader (Jedur, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 2:51",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") are unmistakeable names of places in the list, names which it is not probable were ever borne by persons. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
